#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:0
msgid "# 架构设计与核心特性"
msgstr "# Architecture Design and Core Features"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:2
msgid "## 1.逻辑架构"
msgstr "## 1. Logical Architecture"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:4
msgid ""
"![图像](./figures/architectural_diagram.png)\n"
"**Triton-Ascend 架构说明**\n"
msgstr ""
"![Image](./figures/architectural_diagram.png)\n"
"**Triton-Ascend Architecture Description**\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:6
msgid "**核心组件：**"
msgstr "**Core Components:**"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:8
msgid ""
"- **`Ascend language extension`**：适配 Ascend 的 Triton 语言扩展\n"
"- **`compiler`**：适配 Ascend 的 Triton 编译器\n"
"- **`driver`**：适配 Ascend 的设备驱动接口\n"
msgstr ""
"- **`Ascend language extension`**: Triton language extension adapted for Ascend\n"
"- **`compiler`**: Triton compiler adapted for Ascend\n"
"- **`driver`**: Device driver interface adapted for Ascend\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:10
msgid "**组件功能：**"
msgstr "**Component Functions:**"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:12
msgid ""
"- **`Ascend language extension`**\n"
"  在标准 Triton 语言基础上，引入针对 Ascend NPU 架构的语法与语义扩展。\n"
msgstr ""
"- **`Ascend language extension`**\n"
"  Introduces syntax and semantic extensions tailored for the Ascend NPU architecture based on the standard Triton language.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:14
msgid ""
"- **`compiler`**\n"
"  接收来自上层 Triton compiler 生成的中间表示文件 `TTIR`（Triton IR），执行一系列适配昇腾硬件的转换。\n"
msgstr ""
"- **`compiler`**\n"
"  Receives the intermediate representation file `TTIR` (Triton IR) generated by the upper-layer Triton compiler, and performs a series of transformations adapted to Ascend hardware.\n"

#. type: code
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:16
msgid ""
"  ```python\n"
"  Triton IR → Linalg IR → AscendNPU IR → triton_xxx_kernel.o\n"
"  ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:18
msgid "  Triton IR 转换为 Linalg IR，再经 BiSheng Compiler 生成面向 Ascend NPU 的可执行二进制文件  `triton_xxx_kernel.o`。"
msgstr "Triton IR is converted to Linalg IR, and then through BiSheng Compiler, an executable binary file `triton_xxx_kernel.o` targeting Ascend NPU is generated."

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:20
msgid ""
"- **`driver`**\n"
"  提供 Triton 运行时与 Ascend 软件栈（CANN）之间的对接能力， 加载由 BiSheng Compiler 生成的设备侧可执行内核 `triton_xxx_kernel.o` 。\n"
msgstr ""
"- **`driver`**\n"
"  Provides the interface capability between the Triton runtime and the Ascend software stack (CANN), loading the device-side executable kernel `triton_xxx_kernel.o` generated by the BiSheng Compiler.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:22
msgid "## 2.代码结构"
msgstr "## 2. Code Structure"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:24
msgid "### 2.1 代码结构原则"
msgstr "### 2.1 Code Structure Principles"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:26
msgid "本项目在标准 Triton 基础上，扩展支持华为 Ascend NPU（通过 CANN 软件栈）。整体设计遵循以下**代码原则**："
msgstr "This project extends the standard Triton to support Huawei Ascend NPU (via the CANN software stack). The overall design follows the following **code principles**:"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:28
msgid ""
"> - **若修改与目标硬件无关**（target independent），应保留在 **Triton core** 部分（如language、runtime的通用修改）；\n"
"> - **若修改与 Ascend 硬件强相关**（target affinitive），应放在 **Triton-Ascend** 中。\n"
msgstr ""
"> - **If the modification is target independent**, it should remain in the **Triton core** section (e.g., general modifications to language, runtime);\n"
"> - **If the modification is strongly related to Ascend hardware** (target affinitive), it should be placed in **Triton-Ascend**.\n"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:30
msgid "### 2.2 目录结构与功能说明"
msgstr "### 2.2 Directory Structure and Functional Description"

#. type: text
#: docs/zh/architecture_design_and_core_features.md:32
msgid ""
"| 目录或文件 | 对应架构层级 | 功能说明 |\n"
"| --- | --- | --- |\n"
"| `python/` | Triton core | 保留标准 Triton 的 Python 侧通用实现，包括 `triton.language`、JIT、运行时、缓存、工具链入口等。与硬件无关的通用能力优先放在该目录。 |\n"
"| `include/` 和 `lib/` | Triton core | 保留标准 Triton 的通用 C++/MLIR 基础设施、Dialect、Pass 和转换逻辑。这里不承载 Ascend 专属后端实现。 |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/` | Triton-Ascend | Ascend 后端的根目录，集中放置与 Ascend NPU、CANN、BiSheng Compiler 强相关的语言扩展、编译后端、运行时驱动、MLIR Pass、示例和测试。 |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/language/` | Ascend language extension | Ascend 语言扩展目录，安装后会链接到 `triton.language.extra` 下，供 Triton kernel 通过 `triton.language.extra.cann` 使用。 |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/language/cann/libdevice.py` | Ascend language extension | 适配 Ascend NPU 的 `libdevice` Python 接口，提供数学函数和底层算子封装，供 Triton 算子调用。 |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/backend/compiler.py` | compiler | Ascend 编译器后端主入口，负责注册编译选项、组织 TTIR 到 Ascend 适配 IR、Linalg/LLVM 等阶段的转换，并调用后续工具链生成可执行二进制文件。 |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/backend/driver.py` | driver | Ascend 运行时驱动模块，负责与 CANN/torch_npu 等运行时环境对接，加载并启动已编译的设备侧可执行文件。 |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/include/` 和 `third_party/ascend/lib/` | compiler | Ascend 专属 MLIR Dialect、Pass 和转换实现，例如 `TritonToLinalg`、`TritonToStructured`、`DynamicCVPipeline`、`AutoBlockify` 等。 |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/AscendNPU-IR/` | compiler | Ascend NPU 相关 IR 与 BiSheng 编译链适配内容，是从 Triton-Ascend 编译流程继续下沉到硬件侧代码生成的重要组成部分。 |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/tutorials/` 和 `third_party/ascend/unittest/` | 示例与测试 | 提供 Ascend 平台上的 Triton 示例、迁移样例、Python 单元测试和 MLIR 转换测试，用于验证 Ascend 后端能力。 |\n"
msgstr ""
"| Directory or File | Corresponding Architecture Layer | Functional Description |\n"
"| --- | --- | --- |\n"
"| `python/` | Triton core | Retains the general Python-side implementation of standard Triton, including `triton.language`, JIT, runtime, caching, toolchain entry points, etc. Hardware-independent general capabilities are prioritized in this directory. |\n"
"| `include/` and `lib/` | Triton core | Retains the general C++/MLIR infrastructure, Dialect, Pass, and conversion logic of standard Triton. Ascend-specific backend implementations are not hosted here. |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/` | Triton-Ascend | Root directory of the Ascend backend, centrally hosting language extensions, compilation backend, runtime driver, MLIR Pass, examples, and tests strongly related to Ascend NPU, CANN, and BiSheng Compiler. |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/language/` | Ascend language extension | Ascend language extension directory; after installation, it is linked under `triton.language.extra` for use by Triton kernels via `triton.language.extra.cann`. |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/language/cann/libdevice.py` | Ascend language extension | Python interface of `libdevice` adapted for Ascend NPU, providing mathematical functions and low-level operator wrappers for invocation by Triton operators. |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/backend/compiler.py` | compiler | Main entry point of the Ascend compiler backend, responsible for registering compilation options, orchestrating the conversion from TTIR to Ascend-adapted IR, Linalg/LLVM stages, and invoking subsequent toolchains to generate executable binaries. |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/backend/driver.py` | driver | Ascend runtime driver module, responsible for interfacing with runtime environments such as CANN/torch_npu, loading and launching compiled device-side executables. |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/include/` and `third_party/ascend/lib/` | compiler | Ascend-specific MLIR Dialect, Pass, and conversion implementations, such as `TritonToLinalg`, `TritonToStructured`, `DynamicCVPipeline`, `AutoBlockify`, etc. |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/AscendNPU-IR/` | compiler | Ascend NPU-related IR and BiSheng compilation chain adaptation content, an important component that continues from the Triton-Ascend compilation flow down to hardware-side code generation. |\n"
"| `third_party/ascend/tutorials/` and `third_party/ascend/unittest/` | Examples and Tests | Provides Triton examples, migration samples, Python unit tests, and MLIR conversion tests on the Ascend platform, used to verify the capabilities of the Ascend backend. |\n"

